<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="524" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,356,704]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,428,453]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">Remarks.</emphasis>
The original description gives the 
<typeStatus box="[715,763,429,453]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">type</typeStatus>
as a female, which is an error. However, there is no doubt that the specimen here regarded as the 
<typeStatus box="[610,708,463,488]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">holotype</typeStatus>
is correctly identified because it is the specimen illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zerny" box="[151,315,500,525]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" refString="Zerny, H. (1931 b) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Syntomiden. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 45, 1 - 27 + 1 plate." type="book chapter" year="1931" yearSuffix="b">
Zerny (
<number box="[233,292,500,525]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" value="1931.0">1931</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
, and also it has a label with information provided in the original description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,356,704]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">
The meaning of the first label is unknown. In the second, the holes made by the pin make it impossible to decipher what is written. It could mean that the specimen was illustrated by 
<collectingCountry box="[1005,1073,573,596]" name="Isle of Man" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">Mann</collectingCountry>
, who illustrated many European 
<taxonomicName box="[151,286,607,632]" class="Insecta" family="Acanthopteroctetidae;Agathiphagidae;Alucitidae;Tineodidae;Axiidae;Axiidae;Calocarididae;Micheleidae;Strahlaxiidae;Bombycidae;Brahmaeidae;Carthaeidae;Endromidae;Eupterotidae;Lemoniidae;Mirinidae;Saturniidae;Sphingidae;Callidulidae;Choreutidae;Carposinidae;Copromorphidae;Cossidae;Dudgeoneidae;Drepanidae;Epicopeiidae;Epermeniidae;Eriocraniidae;Galacticidae;Agonoxenidae;Batrachedridae;Blastobasidae;Coleophoridae;Cosmopterigidae;Elachistidae;Ethmiidae;Gelechiidae;Holcopogonidae;Lecithoceridae;Metachandidae;Momphidae;Oecophoridae;Pterolonchidae;Scythrididae;Symmocidae;Geometridae;Sematuridae;Uraniidae;Bucculatricidae;Douglasiidae;Gracillariidae;Roeslerstammiidae;Hedylidae;Anomosetidae;Hepialidae;Neotheoridae;Palaeosetidae;Prototheoridae;Hesperiidae;Heterobathmiidae;Hyblaeidae;Immidae;Adelidae;Cecidosidae;Crinopterygidae;Heliozelidae;Incurvariidae;Prodoxidae;Anthelidae;Lasiocampidae;Lophocoronidae;Micropterigidae;Mimallonidae;Mnesarchaeidae;Neopseustidae;Nepticulidae;Opostegidae;Arctiidae;Doidae;Lymantriidae;Noctuidae;Nolidae;Notodontidae;Oenosandridae;Pantheidae;Palaephatidae;Lycaenidae;Nymphalidae;Papilionidae;Pieridae;Riodinidae;Pterophoridae;Crambidae;Pyralidae;Schreckensteiniidae;Brachodidae;Castniidae;Sesiidae;Simaethistidae;Thyrididae;Acrolophidae;Arrhenophanidae;Eriocottidae;Psychidae;Tineidae;Tischeriidae;Tortricidae;Urodidae;Whalleyanidae;Acrolepiidae;Bedelliidae;Glyphipterigidae;Heliodinidae;Lyonetiidae;Plutellidae;Yponomeutidae;Ypsolophidae;Aididae;Anomoeotidae;Chrysopolomidae;Cyclotornidae;Dalceridae;Epipyropidae;Heterogynidae;Himantopteridae;Lacturidae;Limacodidae;Megalopygidae;Somabrachyidae;Zygaenidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
(but mostly microlepidopterans), if the word reads “abgeb.” (abgebildet, which means “illustrated”).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,356,704]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">
This species is remarkably similar to the illustration of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cramer, 1779" authorityName="Cramer" authorityYear="1779" box="[851,1248,644,669]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Autochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="almon">
<emphasis box="[851,1062,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">Autochloris almon</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cramer" box="[1080,1240,644,668]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" refString="Cramer, P. (1779 - 1780) Papillons exotiques des trois parties du monde, L'Asie, L'Afrique et l'Amerique. Vol. 3. S. J. Baalde, Utrecht, Barthelemy Wild, 176 pp. + plates 193 - 288." type="book chapter" year="1779">
Cramer, 
<number box="[1183,1240,644,668]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" value="1779.0">1779</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
provided in the original description (plate 
<number box="[447,492,680,704]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" value="224.0">224</number>
, fig. F). It is unknown to us whether any of the 
<typeStatus box="[1025,1084,680,704]" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1121,1222,679,704]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Autochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="almon">
<emphasis box="[1121,1222,679,704]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="524">A. almon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still exist.
</paragraph>
